30/01/2008
WASHINGTON, United States -- Albanian Foreign Minister Lulzim Basha met Tuesday (January 29th) with US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice in Washington.
Rice congratulated the Albanian government on the steps taken in fulfilling the standards required by NATO.
She urged Albania to continue a positive dialogue with all NATO member states until the organisation's April summit in Bucharest.
The two officials also discussed the situation in Kosovo.
(Shekulli, Shqip, Koha Jone - 30/01/08;
Balkanweb, Telegrafi, Top-Channel, VOA, AFP - 29/01/08)
